QUALIFICATION: this name is usually mistakenly attributed to Hombron & Jacquinot in Dumont d'Urville, M.J. 1842. Voyage au Pôle Sud et dans l'Océanie sur les corvettes l'Astrolabe et la Zélée, éxecuté pendant les années 1837-40. Atlas Sauriens (1842, pl. 2). [1842-1853], who published only a figure without application of binomial nomenclature. It was subsequenly described by Jacquinot, J. & Guichenot, M.A. 1853. Reptiles et Poissons. In, Dumont d'Urville, M.J. (ed). Voyage au Pôle Sud et dans l'Astrolabe et la Zélée, éxecuté pendant les années 1837-40. Zoologie 3 1-28. Paris : Gide et Baudry, p. 20, who attributed the name to C. Duméril (in ms). The subsequent year Duméril, A.M.C., Bibron, G. & Duméril, A. 1854. Erpétologie Générale ou Histoire Naturelle Complète des Reptiles. Paris : Roret Vol. 7(1) xvi 780 pp. p. 200, also described this taxon as a new 'unpublished species'. The series on which Duméril, Bibron & Duméril based their description included material 'probably from Australia'; this description is included in the above synonymy pending resolution of the authorship and type fixation of Dendrophis lineolata
